Network Forensics > [[Topic 4: Exploring Network Statistics: Insights and Analysis]]

Wireshark provides a comprehensive range of network statistics that can be accessed through the Statistics menu. These statistics cover various aspects, from general information about the loaded capture file to protocol-specific statistics.

Statistics menu - zoom in

1. General Statistics:

  • Capture File Properties: Provides information about the loaded capture file, such as the number of captured packets.
  • Protocol Hierarchy: Displays the hierarchy of protocols observed in the captured packets.
  • Conversations: Shows the traffic between specific IP addresses.
  • Endpoints: Analyzes the traffic to and from specific IP addresses.
  • I/O Graphs: Visualizes the number of packets or similar metrics over time.

2. Protocol-Specific Statistics:

  • Service Response Time: Measures the time between request and response for specific protocols.
  • Various other protocol-specific statistics are available.
